Defendant in custody.    
Defendant is before the Court for sentencing, his probation having been revoked effective 08-08-18.   
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of five (5) years.   Two (2) years initial confinement, followed by three (3) years extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are: 
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Maintain full-time employment/schooling or work search; 
4) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
5) Contact with Mary Rasmussen only as approved by the agent; 
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.   
Defendant is given credit for 158 days already served.   
Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and for the Substance Abuse Program.   
